OL,7,F"I will finish off with this. Let's
OL,8,Fsoldier on and be more like Kirbs. I
OL,9,Flove you, mate."
OL,11,FLouise, his cousin, read a poem in
OL,12,Fmemory of James. It read "Though he's
OL,13,Fjourneyed on, beyond the night. His
OL,14,Flegacy gleams with radiant light.
OL,16,F"So let's celebrate 'Kirbs' with
OL,17,Flaughter and cheer, For James, our
OL,18,Fhero, is always near."
